id: pm-jw36
title: Cache item body in metadata cache for fast keyword search
description: Search keyword was 617ms because every search re-read+parsed all 721 item .toon files for body text. Caching body in front-matter cache (CACHE_VERSION 3 -> 4) reduces warm search to ~140ms (77% speedup). Cold first run rebuilds cache once.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[4]: cache,performance,pm-cli,search
created_at: "2026-05-16T21:54:06.137Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-16T22:55:47.425Z"
author: maintainer-agent
acceptance_criteria: warm search command profile ~140ms (5x faster); list profile unchanged; pm health remains ok; cache invalidates correctly when item file changes.
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: Await metadata-cache persistence and regression-test cached body reuse plus mutation invalidation.
expected_result: Warm keyword search can use cached item bodies deterministically without stale results after item mutation.
actual_result: "Focused linked test, dogfood, and full release gate passed; pm-jw36 closed with cache hit/invalidation evidence."
